"As long as they play their war games, there will be more deaths and innocent people will die," said Hanyecz, whose son joined the Navy at the age of 17.
The dead included one officer, Lt. j.g. Phillip Edward Buch, 24, of Las Cruces, N.M., and 46 enlisted men.
Most victims were single and from 18 to 22 years old, said Navy officials.
Navy officials aboard the Iowa had scheduled firing 22 rounds.
Capt. Larry Seaquist, a former captain of the Iowa, told reporters earlier in the day, "It seems from the reports that those powders exploded."
